<br>
If you are like most followers of a religion, you were indoctrinated at a young age in a belief system and it has carried you thru the rest of your days.  It may not have been LDS (most likely it was) but it was most probably a cult of JC and migration among these cults is not that big a stretch for your core beliefs.  The Jesuites used to say &quot;Give us a child until he is 8 and we have him for life.&quot;  That is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>*VERY*</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> true and most of the reasons people so passionatley defend things lacking reason or cause. There are hordes of systems out there.  Atheists spring from all of them.  They arrived at their conclusions from independant examination, exploration and reason. Yet they all arrived at the same place, because there is no god. <br>
