 is not reasonable to say the least.  Furthermore, implying that our universe is so large that the laws discerned here may have no application elsewhere is further diembling.  How would you propose we codify these far flung laws if we cannot go there to find them?  There is no reason to expect them to run differently from ours locally, but how would you propose we write this fictional rule book <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>en absentia</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> some facts?  Doubt the nuclear forces exist?  Set of an atomic bomb.<br>
